PROBLEM: 'A fair '$6$'-sided die is repeatedly rolled until an odd number appears. What is the probability that every even number appears at least once before the first occurrence of an odd number?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: ~\frac{1}{120}
[B]: ~\frac{1}{32}
[C]: ~\frac{1}{20}
[D]: ~\frac{3}{20}
[E]: ~\frac{1}{6}

PROBLEM: 'A square piece of paper has side length '$1$' and vertices '$A,B,C,$' and '$D$' in that order. As shown in the figure, the paper is folded so that vertex '$C$' meets edge '$\overline{AD}$' at point '$C'$', and edge '$\overline{BC}$' intersects edge '$\overline{AB}$' at point '$E$'. Suppose that '$C'D = \frac{1}{3}$'. What is the perimeter of triangle '$\bigtriangleup AEC' ?$'\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: ~2
[B]: ~1+\frac{2}{3}\sqrt{3}
[C]: ~\frac{13}{6}
[D]: ~1 + \frac{3}{4}\sqrt{3}
[E]: ~\frac{7}{3}
